cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning from partially annotated clips for the task of semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision problem (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning temporally adaptive features to utilize the temporal context in the partially annotated clips, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of slow feature learning, which is a subfield of unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The task of semantic segmentation involves natural language processing (NLP) as well, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of different architecture designs, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
